comments.body:
The issue is that services are not loaded on cloud controllers other than the coordinator as they are not identified as cloud local (as the services are no longer related to the Eucalyptus service)

When components are identified as cloud local they will be in the NOTREADY state on any cloud controllers other than the coordinator since the status check fails (which is how co-location is implemented), this means errors are logged periodically:

{code}
Fri Aug 30 11:50:16 2013 ERROR [Component:Eucalyptus.bootstrap:Futures.class java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker#68] [com.eucalyptus.component.Component$ComponentBootstrapper.doTransition(Component.java):613] java.lang.RuntimeException: The autoscaling service depends upon a locally ENABLED eucalyptus
{code} 

We should either suppress this error logging or use an alternative mechanism to prevent services being enabled on the wrong host. Is is probably least surprising if the services are in the DISABLED state on cloud controllers other than the coordinator (rather than NOTREADY)
